cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with list decoding of homomorphisms between groups, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The groups in question are supersolvable, which is a topic in group theory (cs.GT) and the paper uses techniques from coding theory (cs.CR) and combinatorics (cs.DS) to prove its results.
